com.opengamma.strata.product.rate

Class InflationEndMonthRateObservation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.product.rate.InflationEndMonthRateObservation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RateObservation, Serializable, Bean, ImmutableBean

    public final class InflationEndMonthRateObservation
extends Object
implements RateObservation, ImmutableBean, Serializable
    Defines the observation of inflation figures from a price index where the start index value is known.

    A typical application of this rate observation is payments of a capital indexed bond, where the reference start month is start month of the bond rather than start month of the payment period.

    A price index is typically published monthly and has a delay before publication. The rate observed by this instance will be based on the start index value and the observation relative to the end month.
